April, 1945. As the Allies make their final push in the European 
Theatre, a battle-hardened army sergeant named 
War daddy (Brad Pitt) commands a Sherman tank and 
his five-man crew on a deadly mission behind enemy lines. 
Outnumbered and outgunned, Wardaddy and his men 
face overwhelming odds in their heroic attempts to strike at 
the heart of Nazi Germany.
